    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a great start, it definitely has a strong tone. but for a college paper, i need to anticipate the pushback. people usually argue that meritocracy is a better way to handle things—that if you just focus on individual effort, the wealth will follow and it's more \"fair.\" how should i frame that counter-argument in my essay to show why it's fundamentally flawed or just doesn't work in the real world?",
